http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/Trains-to-be-regulated-for-track-doubling/article13987863.ece

Trains will be regulated on January 9 to take up track-doubling work between Thiruvalla and Changanassery and yard remodelling work at Thiruvalla. Train services between Kollam Junction and Ernakulam railway stations will be affected due to the work, according to the Railways.Full cancellationTrain 66307/66308 Ernakulam Junction-Kollam MEMU leaving Ernakulam Junction at 5.25 a.m. and its return trip from Kollam at 11.10 a.m.; train 56387/56388 Ernakulam-Kayankulam Passenger leaving Ernakulam at 11.30 a.m. and its return trip from Kayamkulam at 5 p.m.; train 56394/56393 Kollam-Kottayam Passenger leaving Kollam at 8.35 a.m. and its return trip from Kottayam at 5.45 p.m. have been cancelled. Train 56381/56382 Ernakulam-Kayamkulam Passenger via Alappuzha leaving at 10 a.m. and its return trip from Kayamkulam at 1 p.m.; train 66302/66301 Ernakulam-Kollam MEMU Via Alappuzha leaving Ernakulam at 8.50 a.m. and its return trip from Kollam at 2.40 p.m. which runs via Kottayam have also been cancelled.Train 56365/56366 Passenger trains between Guruvayur and Punalur will remain partially cancelled between Kottayam and Punalur.Train 2625 Kerala Express to New Delhi, scheduled to depart Thiruvananthapuram Central, will have a delayed start by 45 minutes at 12 noon. Further, the train is likely to be detained for one hour at Kayamkulam or Chengannur.Train 16382 Kanyakumari-Mumbai CST Express; train 12081 Kannur-Thiruvananthapuram Janshatabdi; and train 12626 New Delhi-Thiruvananthapuram Kerala Express will be diverted via Alappuzha with stoppages at Haripad, Ambalappuzha, Alappuzha Cherthala and Ernakulam Junction stations.Special TrainFor the benefit of reserved passengers of Kanyakumari-Mumbai CST Express and passengers reaching Ernakulam on the day by Janshatabdi and Kerala Express, nonstop special passenger trains will be operated between Ernakulam Junction and Kottayam.The special train will start from Ernakulam at 10.30 a.m. and will reach Kottayam at 12 noon. In the return direction, the train will start from Kottayam at 12.15 p.m. to reach Ernakulam Junction at 1.30 p.m.